<dl id="n01016b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01016b">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01016b"> 16(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Buffoon Buffon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Yet, if as <mark>Buffon</mark> implied, beauty of style lies in the number, coherence, and justness of relations between the perceptions evoked <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> then it is evident that beauties of detail which lack organic relation to the whole <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> must, like cut or wired flowers doomed to sterility, ill compare with blooms on thriving plants. <small> T. Sturge Moore, <a name="TSMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TSMS"><cite title="source">&ldquo;The Story of Tristram and Isolt in Modern Poetry&rdquo;</cite></a> in <cite a>The Criterion</cite></a>, I.1 (Oct 1922) 49</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05101g" href="c05all.htm#c05101g">VI.C.05:101(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
